      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="marcelofiore.xml" title="Marcelo Fiore" addr="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>29</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>17589</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00M8</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00M8.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Surjection">Surjection</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is said to be <fr:em><fr:strong>surjective</fr:strong></fr:em> or a<fr:em><fr:strong>surjection</fr:strong></fr:em> when for we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  b\in  B\mathpunct {.} \exists  a\in  A\mathpunct {.} f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex>. A function satisfying this condition is written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow  B]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="marcelofiore.xml" title="Marcelo Fiore" addr="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>22</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>17590</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00KI</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00KI.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Closure of functions under identity and composition">Closure of <fr:link href="jms-00KF.xml" title="Function" addr="jms-00KF" type="local">functions</fr:link> under <fr:link href="jms-00II.xml" title="The identity relation" addr="jms-00II" type="local">identity</fr:link> and <fr:link href="jms-00IN.xml" title="Relational composite" addr="jms-00IN" type="local">composition</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p><fr:link href="jms-00KF.xml" title="Function" addr="jms-00KF" type="local">Functions</fr:link> are closed under <fr:link href="jms-00II.xml" title="The identity relation" addr="jms-00II" type="local">identity</fr:link> and <fr:link href="jms-00IN.xml" title="Relational composite" addr="jms-00IN" type="local">composition</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>22</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>7473</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6029</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-6029.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>We have already seen in <fr:link href="jms-00K8.xml" title="Closure of partial functions under identity and composition" addr="jms-00K8" type="local">Theorem <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00K8" /></fr:link> that <fr:link href="jms-00K7.xml" title="Partial function" addr="jms-00K7" type="local">partial functions</fr:link> are closed under <fr:link href="jms-00II.xml" title="The identity relation" addr="jms-00II" type="local">identity</fr:link> and <fr:link href="jms-00IN.xml" title="Relational composite" addr="jms-00IN" type="local">composition</fr:link>. Therefore, it suffices to argue that the <fr:link href="jms-00II.xml" title="The identity relation" addr="jms-00II" type="local">identity</fr:link> <fr:link href="jms-00K7.xml" title="Partial function" addr="jms-00K7" type="local">partial function</fr:link> is total, and that the <fr:link href="jms-00IN.xml" title="Relational composite" addr="jms-00IN" type="local">composition</fr:link> of two <fr:link href="jms-00KF.xml" title="Function" addr="jms-00KF" type="local">total</fr:link> <fr:link href="jms-00K7.xml" title="Partial function" addr="jms-00K7" type="local">partial functions</fr:link> is <fr:link href="jms-00KF.xml" title="Function" addr="jms-00KF" type="local">total</fr:link>.</fr:p>

 <fr:ol><fr:li>We must show that for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a' \in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {\mathsf {id}_{A}} a']]></fr:tex>; unfolding the definition of the <fr:link href="jms-00II.xml" title="The identity relation" addr="jms-00II" type="local">identity relation</fr:link> we may choose <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a' = a]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Given <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g\colon  A \to  C]]></fr:tex>, we must check that for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, there exists some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[c\in  C]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (g\circ  f\right )\mathclose {}}}c]]></fr:tex>. By the definition of <fr:link href="jms-00IN.xml" title="Relational composite" addr="jms-00IN" type="local">relational composition</fr:link>, we must show that there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[c\in  C]]></fr:tex> and such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {f}b]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\mathrel {c}]]></fr:tex>. We choose <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b = f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[c = g{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}}=g{\mathopen {}\left (f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="marcelofiore.xml" title="Marcelo Fiore" addr="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>17</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>17591</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00IN</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00IN.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Relational composite">Relational composite</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Given <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relations</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } B]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S\colon  B\mathbin {\nrightarrow } C]]></fr:tex>, we can define the <fr:em><fr:strong>relational composite</fr:strong></fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S\circ  R\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } C]]></fr:tex> in a way that generalises composition of functions. In particular, we define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S\circ  R]]></fr:tex> to be the following subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\times  C]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p>
            <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \begin {aligned}
 S\circ  R &\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } C\\
  S\circ  R &=
  {\mathopen {}\left \{
   {\mathopen {}\left (a,c\right )\mathclose {}}\in  A\times  C
   \mid 
   \exists  b\in  B\mathpunct {.}
   a\mathrel {R}b \land  b\mathrel {S} c
  \right \}\mathclose {}}
 \end {aligned}
]]></fr:tex>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
              <fr:contributor>
                <fr:link href="marcelofiore.xml" title="Marcelo Fiore" addr="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
              </fr:contributor>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
              <fr:month>1</fr:month>
              <fr:day>17</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>17592</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-00II</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-00II.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="The identity relation">The identity <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>For any set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, we can form the <fr:em><fr:strong>identity <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></fr:strong></fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {id}_{A}\colon  A\mathbin {\nrightarrow } A]]></fr:tex>, also called the <fr:em><fr:strong>equality <fr:link href="jms-00I7.xml" title="Relation" addr="jms-00I7" type="local">relation</fr:link></fr:strong></fr:em>, which relates each element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to itself. In other words, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\mathrel {\mathsf {id}_{A}} a']]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a=a']]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
